cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ITU and Astrobiology / SETI: A Single-Axiom View of K-Life Emergence, Drake Equation, Habitability, Biosignatures, and the Fermi Paradox"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209; current version v2.0.0 at 10.5281/zenodo.20133709) to astrobiology and
  SETI. Life is reframed as self-replicating K-flow patterns, with
  information content spanning 22 orders of magnitude from viruses
  (10^4 bits) to projected ASI (10^26 bits). The Drake equation is
  reinterpreted as a K-state cascade probability. This is Tier 1
  paper #12, opening the cosmic axis and bringing the ITU polytope
  to 12 vertices. Pass-1 progress: 90 of 220 phases (40.9%).
  Phase 87 establishes the ITU foundation. K_life information content
  ranges 22 orders of magnitude. Drake Monte Carlo with lognormal
  priors gives N median = 0.27 civilizations/galaxy (67% with N < 1).
  Habitability Index ranks exoplanets: Earth 1.00, Teegarden b 0.58,
  TOI-700d 0.45, TRAPPIST-1e 0.41, Proxima b 0.36, Kepler-452b 0.13.
  Fermi paradox 12-hypothesis ITU weighting: Great Filter combined
  65% (past 40% + future 25%), Rare Earth 15%, Dark Forest 8%.
  Phase 88 applies the Sandberg-Drexler-Ord 2018 log-uniform Drake
  approach. P(alone in galaxy) = 87% (Sandberg 53%), P(alone in
  observable universe) = 33% (Sandberg 30%). Carter-Watson hard step
  analysis identifies 2 hard steps: Eukaryote (2.0 Gyr delay) and
  Intelligence (Tier 1 #9 K_self HARD criterion). SDA shows Type II
  Dyson sphere detection range = 6e9 ly (60,000x galactic diameter),
  meaning absence of Type II is informative. Bayesian update from
  Breakthrough Listen null result reduces near-ETI probability
  10% -> 2.2% (5x reduction).
  Phase 89 examines abiogenesis and intelligence emergence as K-state
  phase transitions. RNA world autocatalytic dynamics: low initial
  K_0 still reaches half-max in ~16 time units (inevitable given
  bootstrap). Cambrian explosion phyla diversification 2x speedup
  vs pre-Cambrian, with post-Cambrian rate essentially zero (all
  phyla emerge in Cambrian). Encephalization Quotient vs K_self
  degree across 12 organisms shows log-log correlation r = 0.902
  (slope 0.669). K2-18b DMS Bayesian: prior 5% -> posterior 30%
  given Madhusudhan 2023 2.4 sigma tentative detection.
  Phase 90 synthesises the 2026-2100 roadmap with 17 milestones and
  10 falsifiable predictions (P_avg = 0.61). Key milestones: 2027
  K2-18b DMS 5 sigma judgement, 2040 HWO launch, 2045 first
  confirmed biosignature (P=0.4), 2050 UN ETI contact protocol,
  2055 Proxima b flyby (Starshot), 2100 Fermi resolution.
  The ITU 12-vertex polytope completes by adding the cosmic axis.
  Astrobiology vertex bidirectionally connects Climate (#11),
  AI/ASI (#2), Aging (#6), Free Will (#9), and Tier 0 (life
  self-organization). Climate (#11) remains super-hub at degree 7.
  Central thesis: life is self-replicating K-flow; intelligence is
  K_self degree (continuous spectrum); Fermi silence is consistent
  with Sandberg log-uniform priors and Great Filter at past hard
  steps. Pass-1 interpretive paper reframing Drake, Sandberg,
  Hanson, Carter-Watson, Madhusudhan, Lenton, Lingam-Loeb,
  Breakthrough Listen, JWST exoplanet observations in ITU language.
  Pass-2 work would derive ITU-specific biosignature combinations,
  technosignature search strategies, and quantitative constraints
  on Drake factors f_l and f_i from K-state phase-transition theory.
